  "prompt": "What are the differences between faith, belief, hope and trust?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of the differences between faith, belief, hope, and trust:\n\nFaith:\n- Strong conviction not necessarily based on proof\n- Often associated with spiritual or religious context\n- Involves complete acceptance without absolute evidence\n- Can transcend rational understanding\n- More comprehensive and deeper than belief\n\nBelief:\n- Acceptance that something is true or exists\n- Can be based on evidence, personal experience, or information\n- More intellectual and specific than faith\n- Can be about facts, ideas, or concepts\n- Doesn't necessarily require emotional commitment\n\nHope:\n- Optimistic expectation or desire for a positive outcome\n- Forward-looking and anticipatory\n- Involves emotional desire and positive anticipation\n- Less certain than faith or belief\n- Can exist despite potential uncertainty\n- Provides emotional comfort and motivation\n\nTrust:\n- Confidence in reliability, truth, or ability of someone/something\n- Based on past experiences and proven track record\n- Involves vulnerability and willingness to depend on another\n- More relational and interpersonal\n- Requires demonstrated credibility\n- Can be earned or lost through actions\n\nKey differences:\n- Faith is most comprehensive and spiritual\n- Belief is more intellectual\n- Hope is emotionally optimistic\n- Trust is based on proven reliability",
